explanation: Utilizes a dictionary to store key-value pairs and a list to track the order of key usage.  Retrieving and updating values takes constant time due to dictionary lookups.  Evicting the least recently used item is also O(1) as it involves removing the first element from the list.  Space complexity is directly proportional to the cache capacity.

